# AccessHub

> Open-source platform for accessibility, inclusion and nonprofit organization management.

AccessHub is an open-source platform designed to help nonprofit organizations, disability associations, and community initiatives modernize the way they manage members, digital accessibility, and inclusive services.

The project was born from a real-world need observed in a local disability association that still relies on paper records and physical membership cards. Instead of creating a solution for a single organization, AccessHub aims to become a reusable platform that any nonprofit can deploy, customize and improve.

## Why?

Many disability organizations operate with limited budgets and outdated tools.

Common challenges include:

* Paper-based member records
* Physical membership cards without online validation
* No centralized document management
* Limited accessibility features
* Difficult reporting and statistics
* Lack of digital self-service for members

AccessHub seeks to solve these problems through an open-source, community-driven platform.

## Planned Features

* Member management
* Digital membership cards
* QR Code validation
* Public card verification
* Volunteer management
* Event management
* Accessible dashboard
* AI-powered assistant
* Reports and analytics
* Multi-organization support

## Accessibility First

Accessibility is not an optional feature.

The platform is being designed following accessibility best practices from the beginning.

## Open Source

We welcome contributors from all backgrounds.

Whether you are a developer, designer, accessibility specialist, translator or nonprofit volunteer, your contribution is welcome.

